 :tx/rationale "Create task: DAEMON-7: RFL-2/AR-2 migration to W_alpha — wire operational telemetry to working set instead of shared store (INV-STORE-013, INV-STORE-014, FD-012, ADR-STORE-019). BACKGROUND: This is THE task that fixes the 30s cache invalidation. Currently main.rs writes RFL-2 action predictions (line ~231) and AR-2 reconciliation traces (line ~249) to the shared store via layout.write_tx(). Each write changes the txn fingerprint, invalidating store.bin and fitness.json caches. With W_alpha, these go to in-memory working set instead. APPROACH: (1) In daemon mode: main.rs post-command hook checks if daemon is running. If yes, send RFL-2/AR-2 datoms to daemon's W_alpha via socket command {cmd: 'record_telemetry', datoms: [...]}. (2) In embedded mode (fallback): write RFL-2/AR-2 to .braid/.cache/telemetry.jsonl (append-only local journal, NOT in txns/). This file is read by the daemon on startup. (3) Classification function: is_operational_telemetry(rationale: &str) -> bool. Returns true for 'RFL-2', 'AR-2', 'ST-1 auto-detect'. Returns false for everything else. (4) In main.rs: replace layout.write_tx(&rfl2_tx) with conditional: if daemon running, record_telemetry(). Else append to telemetry journal. ACCEPTANCE: (A) braid status no longer creates txn files in txns/ (only W_alpha/journal). (B) txn fingerprint unchanged after braid status (verified by checking file count). (C) RFL-2 datoms still queryable via daemon (W_alpha merged view). (D) RFL-2 datoms NOT visible in embedded mode query (they're in journal, not store). (E) R(t) weight learning still has access to prediction data (via daemon query or journal replay). DEPENDS-ON: DAEMON-3 (W_alpha), DAEMON-5 (CLI client). FILE: crates/braid/src/main.rs, crates/braid/src/daemon.rs. TRACES-TO: INV-STORE-013, INV-STORE-014, ADR-STORE-019."
